background-repeat: no-repeat;\" data-mw=\"interface\" data-style=\"0\" data-width=\"300\" data-height=\"300\" data-zoom=\"2\" data-lat=\"3934\" data-lon=\"3294\" data-mapid=\"0\" data-plane=\"1\" data-overlays=\"[&quot;_069bc827c946b86ced55a63441e4a12ee6b38c2d&quot;]\" href=\"/w/Special:Map/0/2/1/3294/3934\"></a><a class=\"mw-kartographer-map mw-kartographer-container center\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 300px;background-image: url(https://maps.runescape.wiki/osrs/versions/2022-03-23_a/tiles/rendered/0/2/1_53_56.png), url(https://maps.runescape.wiki/osrs/versions/2022-03-23_a/tiles/rendered/0/2/1_54_56.png), url(https://maps.runescape.wiki/osrs/versions/2022-03-23_a/tiles/rendered/0/2/1_53_55.png), url(https://maps.runescape.wiki/osrs/versions/2022-03-23_a/tiles/rendered/0/2/1_54_55.png), url(https://maps.runescape.wiki/osrs/versions/2022-03-23_a/tiles/rendered/0/2/1_53_54.png), url(https://maps.runescape.wiki/osrs/versions/2022-03-23_a/tiles/rendered/0/2/1_54_54.png); background-position: -74px -242px, 182px -242px, -74px 14px, 182px 14px, -74px 270px, 182px 270px; background-repeat: no-repeat;\" data-mw=\"interface\" data-style=\"0\" data-width=\"300\" data-height=\"300\" data-zoom=\"2\" data-lat=\"3550\" data-lon=\"3448\" data-mapid=\"0\" data-plane=\"1\" data-overlays=\"[&quot;_91096c434c5f5fbf3b502a5debe91c4cd7968ca0&quot;]\" href=\"/w/Special:Map/0/2/1/3448/3550\"></a></td></tr><tr class=\"advanced-data\"><th colspan=\"20\" class=\"infobox-subheader\">Advanced data</th></tr><tr class=\"advanced-data\"><td colspan=\"20\" class=\"infobox-padding\"></td></tr><tr class=\"advanced-data\"><th colspan=\"8\">NPC ID</th><td colspan=\"12\">3455</td></tr><tr class=\"advanced-data\"><td colspan=\"20\" class=\"infobox-padding\"></td></tr></tbody></table><div class=\"infobox-smw-data\" style=\"display:none\"></div>\n<div class=\"floatleft\"><a href=\"/w/File:Viggora_chathead.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Viggora chathead.png\" src=\"/images/Viggora_chathead.png?669c6\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"70\" height=\"109\" data-file-width=\"70\" data-file-height=\"109\" /></a></div>\n<p><b>General Viggora</b> was once a powerful and vicious <a href=\"/w/Human\" title=\"Human\">human</a> warrior of the late <a href=\"/w/Second_Age\" title=\"Second Age\">Second Age</a>. He was one of the few <a href=\"/w/Zaros\" title=\"Zaros\">Zarosian</a> generals, and the only of them to be human. He built the <a href=\"/w/Slayer_Tower\" title=\"Slayer Tower\">Slayer Tower</a> also known as Viggora's Folly, a massive and dark tower of <a href=\"/w/Morytania\" title=\"Morytania\">Morytania</a> that holds many horrific beasts that require a special technique in order to be slain. Despite being a Zarosian general during the Second Age, he eventually stopped following Zaros, and became a follower of <a href=\"/w/Zamorak\" title=\"Zamorak\">Zamorak</a>, who was another Zarosian general at that time. Viggora was a powerful general despite being a human, having possessed a powerful <a href=\"/w/Viggora%27s_chainmace\" title=\"Viggora&#39;s chainmace\">chainmace</a> and used it during his conquests.\n</p><p>He assaulted Zaros' castle with Zamorak,  who was trying to become a <a href=\"/w/God\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God\">god</a> by overcoming Zaros. He watched Zamorak surprisingly defeat the Empty Lord and ascend to godhood as a result. However, when Zaros fell, Zaros cursed all those who played a role in Zamorak's plot, and, since Viggora was human and had a much shorter lifespan than the others, the curse was stronger on him, turning him into an invisible ghost for the rest of eternity. Since the other Zamorakians were alive much longer and had longer lifespans still, the curse of Zaros had a much less harmful effect on them and it is unknown what these effects even were. Following his demise, his chainmace was claimed by another Zamorakian follower who eventually perished in the <a href=\"/w/Wilderness\" title=\"Wilderness\">Wilderness</a> and returned as a <a href=\"/w/Revenant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Revenant\">revenant</a>.\n</p><p>He is the last character the player must speak to in the <a href=\"/w/Curse_of_the_Empty_Lord\" title=\"Curse of the Empty Lord\">Curse of the Empty Lord</a> <a href=\"/w/Miniquest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Miniquest\">miniquest</a>, and explains much of the story of <a href=\"/w/Zamorak\" title=\"Zamorak\">Zamorak</a>'s betrayal of <a href=\"/w/Zaros\" title=\"Zaros\">Zaros</a>. A <a href=\"/w/Ring_of_visibility\" title=\"Ring of visibility\">ring of visibility</a> and a <a href=\"/w/Ghostspeak_amulet\" title=\"Ghostspeak amulet\">ghostspeak amulet</a> must be worn in order to see him and communicate with him.\n</p><p>Viggora the Warrior can be found at one of the following locations, specific to each player:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Paddewwa\" title=\"Paddewwa\">Paddewwa</a>, <a href=\"/w/Edgeville_Dungeon\" title=\"Edgeville Dungeon\">Edgeville Dungeon</a>, inside the far room with the <a href=\"/w/Earth_warrior\" title=\"Earth warrior\">earth warriors</a>.</li>\n<li><span class=\"floornumber\"><span class=\"floornumber-gb\">1<sup class=\"floornumber-ordinal-suffix\">st</sup>&#160;floor<sup class=\"floornumber-help noexcerpt\">&#91;<span class=\"fact-text floor-convention\" title=\"British convention; floor 2 in the US\">UK</span>&#93;</sup></span><span class=\"floornumber-us noexcerpt\">2<sup class=\"floornumber-ordinal-suffix\">nd</sup>&#160;floor<sup class=\"floornumber-help noexcerpt\">&#91;<span class=\"fact-text floor-convention\" title=\"US convention; floor 1 in the UK\">US</span>&#93;</sup></span></span> of the <a href=\"/w/Rogues%27_Castle\" title=\"Rogues&#39; Castle\">Rogues' Castle</a> in the deep <a href=\"/w/Wilderness\" title=\"Wilderness\">Wilderness</a>.</li>\n<li><span class=\"floornumber\"><span class=\"floornumber-gb\">1<sup class=\"floornumber-ordinal-suffix\">st</sup>&#160;floor<sup class=\"floornumber-help noexcerpt\">&#91;<span class=\"fact-text floor-convention\" title=\"British convention; floor 2 in the US\">UK</span>&#93;</sup></span><span class=\"floornumber-us noexcerpt\">2<sup class=\"floornumber-ordinal-suffix\">nd</sup>&#160;floor<sup class=\"floornumber-help noexcerpt\">&#91;<span class=\"fact-text floor-convention\" title=\"US convention; floor 1 in the UK\">US</span>&#93;</sup></span></span> of the <a href=\"/w/Canifis\" title=\"Canifis\">Canifis</a> <a href=\"/w/Slayer_Tower\" title=\"Slayer Tower\">Slayer Tower</a>, just before the <a href=\"/w/Infernal_Mage\" title=\"Infernal Mage\">Infernal Mages</a>, in the narrow hallway after the stairs (take a nose peg or Slayer helmet if using the spiked chain shortcut. Bring a ghostspeak amulet, in addition to your ring of visibility).</li></ul>\n<p>After hearing his story, you'll receive a <a href=\"/w/Ghostly_cloak\" title=\"Ghostly cloak\">Ghostly cloak</a> from him.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Treasure_Trails\">Treasure Trails</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Viggora?section=1&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Treasure Trails\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Viggora?action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Treasure Trails\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Viggora is the solution to the master <a href=\"/w/Treasure_Trails/Guide/Cryptic_clues\" title=\"Treasure Trails/Guide/Cryptic clues\">cryptic clue</a>: <i>Come brave adventurer, your sense is on fire. If you talk to me, it's an old god you desire.</i> Players must have completed the <a href=\"/w/Curse_of_the_Empty_Lord\" title=\"Curse of the Empty Lord\">Curse of the Empty Lord</a> miniquest up until the point where the player needs to talk to Viggora. After the miniquest, be sure to bring a <a href=\"/w/Ghostspeak_amulet\" title=\"Ghostspeak amulet\">ghostspeak amulet</a> (<a href=\"/w/Morytania_legs_2\" title=\"Morytania legs 2\">Morytania legs 2</a>, <a href=\"/w/Morytania_legs_3\" title=\"Morytania legs 3\">Morytania legs 3</a>, and <a href=\"/w/Morytania_legs_4\" title=\"Morytania legs 4\">Morytania legs 4</a> also work), as well as a <a href=\"/w/Ring_of_visibility\" title=\"Ring of visibility\">ring of visibility</a>. Viggora will be in the same place as during the miniquest, which is written in the miniquest log.\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Changes\">Changes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Viggora?section=2&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Changes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Viggora?action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Changes\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible sortable\" style=\"max-width:800px\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Date\n</th>\n<th>Changes\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/w/9_April\" title=\"9 April\">9&#160;April</a>&#160;<a href=\"/w/2015\" title=\"2015\">2015</a><br />(<a href=\"/w/Update:Motherlode_Expansion_%26_More\" title=\"Update:Motherlode Expansion &amp; More\">update</a>)\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Gravingas &amp; the Ghosts from the Curse of Zaros miniquest now recognize the Morytania legs built-in ghostspeak function.\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"navbox nowraplinks mw-collapsible\" data-expandtext=\"show\" data-navbox-name=\"Curse of the Empty Lord\" data-collapsetext=\"hide\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"navbox-title\" id=\"navbox-title\"><div class=\"navbox-title-name-notplain\"><div class=\"navbar\" style=\"float:left;text-align:left;width:6em\"><div class=\"plainlinks noprint\" style=\"background-color:transparent;padding:0;font-weight:normal;font-size:xx-small;white-space:nowrap\"><a href=\"/w/Template:Curs