5px-Dhalak_chathead.png?08ff8 2x\" data-file-width=\"119\" data-file-height=\"150\" /></a></span><a href=\"/w/Dhalak\" title=\"Dhalak\">Dhalak</a></li>\n<li><span class=\"plink-template\"><a href=\"/w/Viggora\" title=\"Viggora\"><img alt=\"Viggora chathead.png: Chat head image of Viggora\" src=\"/images/thumb/Viggora_chathead.png/22px-Viggora_chathead.png?669c6\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"22\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/Viggora_chathead.png/34px-Viggora_chathead.png?669c6 1.5x, /images/thumb/Viggora_chathead.png/45px-Viggora_chathead.png?669c6 2x\" data-file-width=\"70\" data-file-height=\"109\" /></a></span><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Viggora</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\">Other</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Transcript:Curse_of_the_Empty_Lord\" title=\"Transcript:Curse of the Empty Lord\">Transcript</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/The_General%27s_Shadow\" title=\"The General&#39;s Shadow\">The General's Shadow</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Ring_of_visibility\" title=\"Ring of visibility\">Ring of visibility</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Ghostspeak_amulet\" title=\"Ghostspeak amulet\">Ghostspeak amulet</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mediawiki‐67df7655d‐7qtxl\nCached time: 20220420205000\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.126 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.158 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 526/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 19236/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1137/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3293/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.046/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1598945/367001600 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   98.863      1 -total\n 51.03%   50.454      1 Template:Infobox_NPC\n 17.81%   17.610      1 Template:Curse_of_the_Empty_Lord\n 17.01%   16.813      3 Template:Map\n 13.21%   13.063      1 Template:External\n 12.00%   11.862      1 Template:Navbox\n  8.23%    8.133      2 Template:FloorNumber\n  3.70%    3.657      1 Template:Ctg\n  2.78%    2.750      1 Template:Subject_changes\n  2.38%    2.356      1 Template:CrypticNPC\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:42578-0!canonical and timestamp 20220420204959 and revision id 14261365. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{External|rs}}\n{{Otheruses2|def=no|his [[mace]]|Viggora's chainmace}}\n{{Infobox NPC\n|name = Mysterious ghost\n|image = [[File:Viggora.png|120px]]\n|release = [[26 July]] [[2005]]\n|update = The Forgettable Tale...\n|members = Yes\n|race = [[Ghost]]\n|quest = [[Curse of the Empty Lord]]\n|location = [[Edgeville Dungeon]], [[Slayer Tower]], [[Rogues' Castle]]\n|gender = Male\n|options = Talk-To\n|examine = {{*}} Seems to flitter in and out of existence...<br/>{{*}} The ghost of a powerful warrior that remains trapped in the Shadow Realm.\n|map = {{Map|name=Viggora|x=3119|y=9996|plane=0|r=4|mapID=-1|mtype=square}}{{Map|name=Viggora|x=3294|y=3934|plane=1|r=4|mapID=0|mtype=square}}{{Map|name=Viggora|x=3448|y=3550|plane=1|r=4|mapID=0|mtype=square}}\n|id = 3455\n}}\n[[File:Viggora chathead.png|left]]\n'''General Viggora''' was once a powerful and vicious [[human]] warrior of the late [[Second Age]]. He was one of the few [[Zaros]]ian generals, and the only of them to be human. He built the [[Slayer Tower]] also known as Viggora's Folly, a massive and dark tower of [[Morytania]] that holds many horrific beasts that require a special technique in order to be slain. Despite being a Zarosian general during the Second Age, he eventually stopped following Zaros, and became a follower of [[Zamorak]], who was another Zarosian general at that time. Viggora was a powerful general despite being a human, having possessed a powerful [[Viggora's chainmace|chainmace]] and used it during his conquests.\n\nHe assaulted Zaros' castle with Zamorak,  who was trying to become a [[god]] by overcoming Zaros. He watched Zamorak surprisingly defeat the Empty Lord and ascend to godhood as a result. However, when Zaros fell, Zaros cursed all those who played a role in Zamorak's plot, and, since Viggora was human and had a much shorter lifespan than the others, the curse was stronger on him, turning him into an invisible ghost for the rest of eternity. Since the other Zamorakians were alive much longer and had longer lifespans still, the curse of Zaros had a much less harmful effect on them and it is unknown what these effects even were. Following his demise, his chainmace was claimed by another Zamorakian follower who eventually perished in the [[Wilderness]] and returned as a [[revenant]].\n\nHe is the last character the player must speak to in the [[Curse of the Empty Lord]] [[miniquest]], and explains much of the story of [[Zamorak]]'s betrayal of [[Zaros]]. A [[ring of visibility]] and a [[ghostspeak amulet]] must be worn in order to see him and communicate with him.\n\nViggora the Warrior can be found at one of the following locations, specific to each player:\n*[[Paddewwa]], [[Edgeville Dungeon]], inside the far room with the [[earth warrior]]s.\n*{{FloorNumber|uk=1}} of the [[Rogues' Castle]] in the deep [[Wilderness]].\n*{{FloorNumber|uk=1}} of the [[Canifis]] [[Slayer Tower]], just before the [[Infernal Mage]]s, in the narrow hallway after the stairs (take a nose peg or Slayer helmet if using the spiked chain shortcut. Bring a ghostspeak amulet, in addition to your ring of visibility).\n\nAfter hearing his story, you'll receive a [[Ghostly cloak]] from him.\n\n==Treasure Trails==\n{{CrypticNPC|Viggora|master|Come brave adventurer, your sense is on fire. If you talk to me, it's an old god you desire.}} Players must have completed the [[Curse of the Empty Lord]] miniquest up until the point where the player needs to talk to Viggora. After the miniquest, be sure to bring a [[ghostspeak amulet]] ([[Morytania legs 2]], [[Morytania legs 3]], and [[Morytania legs 4]] also work), as well as a [[ring of visibility]]. Viggora will be in the same place as during the miniquest, which is written in the miniquest log.\n\n\n==Changes==\n{{Subject changes header}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 9 April 2015\n|update = Motherlode Expansion & More\n|change = Gravingas & the Ghosts from the Curse of Zaros miniquest now recognize the Morytania legs built-in ghostspeak function.\n}}\n{{Subject changes footer}}\n\n{{Curse of the Empty Lord}}\n[[Category:Zamorakians]]"}